          "body": "Psalm 90 sits at the threshold of Book IV of the Psalter (Pss. 90-106), the book that responds to the collapse of the Davidic covenant in Psalm 89 by enthroning YHWH Himself as eternal King (Pss. 93, 95-99). In that placement, the only psalm of Moses introduces the answer to the failure of human kingship: not a stronger David, but the eternal God who has been the dwelling place from generation to generation. The New Testament picks up v.4 directly in 2 Peter 3:8 to ground patience in God's reckoning of time, and the petition of v.17 — that the work of our hands be confirmed — finds its ultimate yes in the resurrection, where mortal work in Christ is not in vain (1 Corinthians 15:58). The eternal dwelling place (v.1) becomes the Father's house with many rooms (John 14:2), and the heart of wisdom (v.12) is the wisdom hidden in Christ (Colossians 2:3)."
